itemLabel: William Cullen, Baron Cullen of Whitekirk

wikipedia_page.main: William Douglas Cullen, Baron Cullen of Whitekirk,  (born 18 November 1935) is a former senior member of the Scottish judiciary. He formerly served as Lord Justice General and Lord President of the Court of Session, and was an additional Lord of Appeal in the House of Lords prior to the transfer of its judicial functions to the Supreme Court.
